  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accountant (SEA)",
  "description": "<p>The Accountant provides full and proper accounting for all Southeast Asian entities of the Cleantech Group, contributing to accurate financial representation of the Group.  <br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities </strong>(including but not limited to):<br /><br /><strong>Full Set of Accounts for SEA Entities </strong></p><ul><li>Maintain full set of accounts for SEA entities, including GL, AR, AP, fixed assets, and cash</li></ul><ul><li>Perform month-end closing activities for SEA entities, including journal entries, accruals, prepayments, and reconciliations</li></ul><ul><li>Process and post vendor invoices, including prepare AP ageing and ensure timely payments in line with cash flow planning</li></ul><ul><li>AR responsibilities including customer invoicing, accurate AR posting, ageing monitoring, and collection follow-ups.</li></ul><ul><li>Monitor and control project costs and WIP by tracking actuals, commitments, and accruals against budgets, preparing WIP schedules, and analysing variances to support accurate reporting and project costs.</li></ul><ul><li>Monthly bank reconciliations for all bank accounts</li></ul><ul><li>Monthly AR, AP, intercompany sub-ledgers reconciliation and prepare balance sheet schedules with proper supporting<br /></li></ul><p><strong>Support for Tax, Audit, Compliance</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for GST lodgments for Singapore entities and VAT for other SEA entities, withholding tax filings, and other local statutory submissions</li></ul><ul><li>Provide data and schedules to in-country external consultants for tax and compliance filings</li></ul><ul><li>Prepare or support preparation of statutory financial statements for SEA entities</li></ul><ul><li>Assist in any other ad-hoc reports or filings, as required<br /></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>3 - 5 years of experience in Finance and Accounting, with prior audit background preferred</li><li>Working knowledge of ERP system – experience in MS Dynamics 365 Business Central highly regarded</li><li>Detail-oriented, self-directed, dependable and highly motivated</li><li>Strong analytical and reconciliation skills</li><li>Able to work in fast-paced and deadline-driven environment to meet tight reporting deadlines</li></ul>",
